data.description: Seamlessly blending luxury, comfort, and modern living while nestled within a serene and sought-after neighborhood in Historic Beaufort, this property provides a truly captivating living experience. The exterior landscaping is meticulously curated, creating a captivating curb appeal that is sure to impress both residents and guests alike. Stepping inside, you'll find a spacious and thoughtfully designed interior that is flooded with natural light. The open floor plan concept enhances the sense of space and allows for seamless transitions between living areas. The living room, adorned with large windows, serves as the heart of the home, offering a welcoming space to relax and entertain. The gourmet kitchen is a masterpiece of both style and functionality. It boasts top-of-the-line appliances, ample counter space, and modern fixtures, catering to the needs of even the most discerning chefs. The master suite is a sanctuary of comfort, featuring a spacious layout, and 2 en-suite bathrooms that rival those found in luxury spas along with 2 closets. The additional bedrooms are equally charming, extending comfortable living spaces with ample closet storage. The property's well-designed layout ensures privacy and tranquility for every member of the household. The backyard is a private oasis with a patio area for al fresco dining, and space for outdoor recreation not to mention the beautiful water view. This space is ideal for hosting gatherings, enjoying sunny days, or simply unwinding in a serene environment. Located in a friendly and well-established community, this property provides easy access to local amenities, schools, parks, and shopping centers. Optional membership to Clubhouse, pool and boat ramp. Also optional just boat ramp membership. Morehead Beaufort Yacht Club
